- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses the representation of data in the lambda calculus and provides a recursion scheme. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is likely because the paper uses a pure type theory and discusses recursive types. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is possible because the paper discusses the Parigot and Scott encodings, which are related to formal language theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible because the paper discusses data representations and provides constant-time destructors.
